			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				yes the range of the arrow is added to the range of the bow, with a range 150 bow and range 150 arrows you can outrange spellcaster any day.<BR>
<BR>
  also don't forget if you are a ranger use your snare and then reverse kite. best way to do this is open the fight with a bow shot, then snare then use a flame lick, after that just run backwards wile letting the arrows do the work for you. you should be able to knock a good 10 or 12 shots before having to aply another snare. only problem with this style of combat is that you would go to arrows like crazy because you would have to use at least 80 arrows to kill something that is blue to you at 23nd level (aviak rooks and darters in south karanas are perfect for this)<BR>
I been able to drop a few even cons with this tactic but it takes a long time to do and is expensive, but its fun to do once in a wile =)<BR>
also don't forget to change your camera angle so you can see where you going =)<BR>
<BR>
    you should always use this tactic wile you are the puller for a group by the way.<BR>
<BR>
  
				</font>
