	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Greetings Fellow Travilers,<BR>
I couldn't Help but notice some one say &quot;Bows are only for Pulling Monsters.&quot;  This is so Untrue! <BR>
With a Very Simple tactics -- Which I'll be Glad to teach In-Game on Cazic-Thule -- You can get Three to four 8-12Damage Hits in Before it ever Swings at you!<BR>
<BR>
So How do I Pull thiss Off?<BR>
-Find something Blue or Higher (My Skills never seem to Raise on Greet Critters, But it Might just be me.) And stand about 50-75 Paces off.<BR>
-Using a Long Bow and Run' he mill &quot;Arrow&quot;s, Shoot at your Target.<BR>
-Run BACKWARDS the Second you get that Arrow off. (It's Helpful if you make sure There's not a Dragon or a Hill Giant or what not behind you.)<BR>
-As you Run Backwards, Fire Arrows.  Unlike Magic, You can Fire and Move at the same Time.<BR>
-When it gets to Malee Range, just hit your &quot;Malee Attack&quot; Butten, no need to change weapons at all.<BR>
<BR>
This will help you Rase your skill, and 15-30 Damage to something before it ever gets to you is a Nice Bounses, Eh?<BR>
Also - Always keep your Archery Maxxed from Day One.  Kill those Rats and buy a &quot;Hunting Bow&quot; if you Can't afford a &quot;long Bow&quot;.  Upgrade when ever Possable!  <BR>
<BR>
Sincerly,<BR>
Nehallie Woodspirit<BR>
Cazic-Thule Server
				</font>
			</td>

